Concept
.......

A game with the feel of early 2D Zeldas. Multiplayer, cooperative.

Combined with the plot / theme of Kurosawa's Seven Samurai (as remade, lifted and adapted in The Magnificent Seven and probably others). There will be an attack on a village. Band together with the other players to collect up the crops and build defenses before the assault of bandits.

Modules Implicated
..................

Note that at least 14 points are required. You get 2 for a major and 1 for a minor.

* User interaction (major)

* Additional browser (minor)
  Simply write the game in portable (whatever)

* Standard User management and authentication (major)

* Game stats and "match" history (minor)

* AI opponent (i.e. the bandits?) (major)

* Implement a complete web-based game where users can play against each other. (major)
  Slight doubt whether co-op play counts as "against". Seems to want "real-time multiplayer" but that includes turn-based games...

* remote players (major)
  If the logic is done properly it should be as easy to have a remote player as a 2nd local one....

* More than 2 players (major)
  I mean we are ripping off *7* Samurai so that should be the goal...

* Customisation (minor)

* Gamification (minor)
    i.e. XP and similar
